About STOmics and Stereo-seq

BGI STOmics is a pioneer in advancing spatially-resolved transcriptomic analysis through its proprietary Stereo-seq (SpaTial Enhanced REsolution Omics-Sequencing) technology. Built on DNA Nanoball (DNB) technology, Stereo-seq offers researchers a novel tool to explore spatial biology with unprecedented field-of-view and resolution. Stereo-seq has been applied to many cutting-edge research projects worldwide. The initial results of these project have been published in world's leading multidisciplinary science such as Cell, Nature, and Science.

What you will experience as a Field Application/Bioinformatics Scientist with BGI STOmics:

· You will be the go-to person for leading life science laboratories that use our technology, and support them to help move their research forward and achieve their goals;
· You will have the opportunity to hit the ground running and get experience working in a commercial setting;
· You will gain working experience in an international company with global exposure;
· You will work with many talented people in a supportive and enjoyable work environment where everyone’s voice is valued.

Key Responsibilities:

· Discuss product offerings with potential and current collaborators;
· Be the go-to person for collaborators on Stereo-seq project related matters and respond in a timely manner;
· Provide application/bioinformatics technical support for collaborators in the design and analysis of experiments;
· Work with our internal scientists to answer specific collaborator-driven biological questions;
· Prepare technical reports, presentations (both internal and external), and manuscripts detailing key methodologies and results;
· Troubleshoot and maintain application/bioinformatics pipelines;
· Be responsible for new technologies technical transfer from HQ to region;
· Represent BGI STOmics and participate in major conferences in the field;
· Feedback market needs to internal Product and R&D department;
· Manage projects according to company regulations.

Education:

· Ph.D. degree with 2+ years (or MS degree with 5+ years) of working experience in the industry in the field of biology, bioinformatics, or equivalent.

Experience / Skill:

· Must be confident and comfortable when working in a customer-facing environment;
· Experience in external technical training is a plus;
· Strong self-directed learning and researching skill for new knowledge is a must;
· Strong technical knowledge of NGS applications and bioinformatics, single cell sequencing and spatial omics experience strongly preferred;
· Solid computational skills and a deep understanding of omics data and its analysis is a plus;
· Proficient in Python is preferred for FAS and required for FBS;
· Excellent personal and communication skills, including solid presentation and writing skills;
· Linguistic and cultural fluency in English required, additional language a plus (any other language at native or near-native proficiency);
· Native or near-native level Chinese proficiency is a plus (speaking, reading, writing);
· Must be self-motivated, a quick learner, dedicated to achieving excellence, and love to take on new challenges;

About BGI
BGI was founded in 1999 in order to participate in the Human Genome Project (HGP), one of the greatest scientific achievements of the last century. Since then, BGI has integrated innovative research, technology and business development with both non-profit and profit operations. With businesses in more than 100 countries and regions around the world, BGI has established cooperation and partnerships with thousands of different organizations across multi-disciplinary research areas including medical health, resource conservation and judicial services. At the same time, BGI provides equipment, technical support and solutions for the needs of national economies and people's livelihoods, such as precision medicine and precision health.
· Mission - Trans-omics for a better life.
